    {
      "cve": {
        "id": "CVE-2018-20377",
        "sourceIdentifier": "cve@mitre.org",
        "published": "2018-12-23T18:29:00.527",
        "lastModified": "2024-11-21T04:01:21.403",
        "vulnStatus": "Modified",
        "cveTags": [],
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "Orange Livebox 00.96.320S devices allow remote attackers to discover Wi-Fi credentials via /get_getnetworkconf.cgi on port 8080, leading to full control if the admin password equals the Wi-Fi password or has the default admin value. This is related to Firmware 01.11.2017-11:43:44, Boot v0.70.03, Modem 5.4.1.10.1.1A, Hardware 02, and Arcadyan ARV7519RW22-A-L T VR9 1.2."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "Los dispositivos Orange Livebox 00.96.320S permiten que atacantes remotos descubran las credenciales wifi mediante /get_getnetworkconf.cgi en el puerto 8080, lo que conduce al control total si la contraseña del administrador es igual a la contraseña de la wifi o tiene el valor \"admin\" por defecto. Esto está relacionado con Firmware 01.11.2017-11:43:44, Boot v0.70.03, Modem 5.4.1.10.1.1A, Hardware 02 y Arcadyan ARV7519RW22-A-L T VR9 1.2."
          }
        ],
